{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"iorxcnsnmhl0hw3ki8w3h2z","title":"Referent","desc":"","updated":1756063907804,"created":1755990922267,"custom":{},"fname":"concept.referent","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"documentation","selfContained":false,"name":"sflo"},"contentHash":"4574ce1cd99fc99fb34a0355407438dd","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"concept.referent","id":"iorxcnsnmhl0hw3ki8w3h2z","vaultName":"sflo"},"value":"resource.node-component.flow.reference","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":54,"offset":685},"end":{"line":19,"column":96,"offset":727},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"resource.node-component.flow.reference"}},{"from":{"fname":"resource.node.bare","id":"bare-node","vaultName":"sflo"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":109,"offset":336},"end":{"line":9,"column":129,"offset":356},"indent":[]},"value":"concept.referent"}],"anchors":{"referent":{"type":"header","text":"Referent","value":"referent","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"p0vd6xnshcxw14ztkglxyxn","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"referent\">Referent<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#referent\"></a></h1>\n<p>Perfect ‚Äî here‚Äôs an extended wiki note that folds in that case:</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"referent-1\">Referent<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#referent-1\"></a></h2>\n<p><strong>Definition</strong>\nThe <em>referent</em> is the thing (real or imaginary) that a node‚Äôs IRI <strong>refers to</strong>. Every node IRI is an identifier for its referent.</p>\n<p><strong>Node vs. referent</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Referent</strong>: the subject that the node‚Äôs IRI names (a person, concept, event, dataset, etc.).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Node</strong>: the mesh construct that manages flows about that referent.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>To talk about the node itself, you use its <strong>node handle</strong> (e.g. published IRI <code>https://ns.example.org/persons/djradon/_node-handle</code> or mesh identifier <code>&#x3C;djradon/_node-handle></code>).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Where it‚Äôs described</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The <strong>referent‚Äôs description</strong> lives in the node‚Äôs <a href=\"/sflo/notes/np4wrgk86b44hnlsjo964nz\">reference flow</a>.</li>\n<li>The <strong>node‚Äôs own metadata and provenance</strong> live in the <strong><code>_node-*</code> flows</strong> (e.g. <code>_node-metadata-flow</code>, <code>_node-config-*</code>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Special case: data nodes</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>In a <strong>data node</strong>, the <strong>referent</strong> is not an external entity but an <strong>evolvable dataset</strong> contained in the node.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The dataset evolves as versioned distributions inside the node‚Äôs <code>_data-flow</code> (e.g. <code>v1/</code>, <code>v2/</code>, ‚Ä¶).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The <code>_ref-flow</code> may describe the dataset, e.g. its <strong>name, type, and provenance</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Node IRI: <code>https://ns.example.org/projects/atlas/</code></li>\n<li>Referent: <em>the Atlas dataset</em> (identified by the node IRI, evolving over time).</li>\n<li><code>_ref-flow</code>: declares it as a dataset, supplies label and attribution.</li>\n<li><code>_data-flow</code>: provides concrete versions (<code>v1</code>, <code>v2</code>, ‚Ä¶).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p>üëâ Would you like me to also draft the <strong>paired wiki note for ‚ÄúNode handle‚Äù</strong>, so your docs have ‚ÄúReferent‚Äù and ‚ÄúNode handle‚Äù defined side-by-side?</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/sflo/notes/bare-node\">bare node</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"voy7zrf0f6bs86m02uadhaf","title":"Semantic Flow Documentation","desc":"","updated":1756155165637,"created":1755709990079,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"documentation","selfConta